article_title: Fee-For-Service Exodus Boosts UnitedHealth By $2 Billion

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: UnitedHealth Group (UNH) says its revenue this year will increase by $2 billion more than earlier projected for 2015 thanks in part to its expansion on public exchanges under the Affordable Care Act and its push to more value-based care contracts with doctors and hospitals.
